    <p class="card__title"> THIRTEEN TRIANGLES   1986 - 1989

</p>
    <p class="card__description">
In Sacred Geometry the triangle pointing upward expresses a longing for wisdom and strength. It indicates need and a desire for evolution. When I 'saw' the Thirteen Triangles in my mind, they had an undeciphered message on the interior of each structure. When they were finished, people stood in the center of them and often could feel something mysterious, a little bit like a vibration or a force of energy, something beneficial. The structures are 4,90 meters on each side and made from canvas, acrylic paint, and collage with metal pieces to attach them.

Magali Michel  art critic (translation)
« The forms in these structures are superbe, rich in color, like a symbol of human balance. They're a harmony between feelings and desire. »
    </p>
